New Records: Congo fielded 12 inexperienced players, including Rabby Nzingoula and Will Hondermarck, in their squad for the match.
Key Match Events: The match was originally scheduled to be played in Kinshasa but was moved to Morocco's Grand Stadium of Agadir due to FIFA approval issues.
Pre-Game Insights: Congo has a poor record against Morocco, having never won in their three meetings, while Morocco is in a strong position after a recent win against Zambia.
